			<title class="- topic/title " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="title:2;10:11">Oxygen Applications</title>
			<p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="p:1;11:7">
				<ul id="ul_v3t_mcs_lwx" class="- topic/ul " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="ul:1;12:29">
					<li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="li:1;13:10"><xref href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/content_fusion.html" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="xref:1;14:25"><?ditaot usertext?><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="b:1;14:28">Oxygen Content Fusion</b></xref> is a <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="b:2;14:69">web-based
							Git-enabled DITA CMS</b>. It is designed to provide the missing pieces
						that Git lacks when working with a DITA project, such as review workflows
						and publishing.</li>
					<li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="li:2;18:10"><xref href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-addons/topics/git-addon.html" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="xref:2;19:39"><?ditaot usertext?><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="b:3;19:42">Git Client</b></xref> add-on in Oxygen
						XML Editor allows you to use Git from the comfort of your authoring
						tool.</li>
					<li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="li:3;22:10"><xref href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/xml_web_author.html" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="xref:3;23:25"><?ditaot usertext?><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="b:4;23:28">Oxygen XML Web Author</b></xref> has support for all
						Git hosting servers. It is customisable and can be integrated with your
						workflows and tools, such as <xref href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/demo/wa_web_author_into_your_documentation_review_workflow.html" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="xref:4;27:39"><?ditaot usertext?>JIRA issue tracking</xref>.</li>
