			<title class="- topic/title " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="title:3;32:11">Repository hosting solutions</title>
			<p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="p:2;33:7">
				<ul id="ul_gjw_5tl_mwb" class="- topic/ul " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="ul:2;34:29">
					<li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="li:4;35:10"><xref href="https://github.com/" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="xref:5;36:9"><?ditaot usertext?>GitHub</xref> (either online or on-premise).</li>
					<li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="li:5;37:10"><xref href="https://about.gitlab.com/" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="xref:6;38:9"><?ditaot usertext?>GitLab</xref> (either online or on-premise).</li>
				</ul>
			</p>
			<p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="p:3;41:7">Both of these solutions come with:<ul id="ul_yxv_ztl_mwb" class="- topic/ul " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="ul:3;41:65">
					<li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="li:6;42:10">Support for creating and managing private/public repositories.</li>
					<li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="li:7;43:10">Basic support for creating and handling tickets/issues.</li>
					<li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/git-tech-writers/git_client_applications.dita" xtrc="li:8;44:10">Support for creating pull/merge requests.</li>
				</ul></p>
		</section>
